The Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) Yobe State Council has appealed to the state government to comply with executive order 10 issued by President Muhammad Buhari two years ago to guarantee the independence of the three arms of government, the local government, judiciary and legislature at the state levels. Comrade Muktar Musa Tarbutu, Chairman of NLC Yobe State Council made the plea on Sunday at a press briefing to mark the May Day 2022 celebration in Damaturu. He said that “in view of the above, the Congress expects the government to comply with section 121 (3), section 162 (9) of the constitution of the federal republic of Nigeria 1999 (as amended)”. Tarbutu further disclosed that “the pronouncement is supported by (3) pronouncement of the court’s decision in the case of Olisa Agbakkogba vs AG Ekiti state, Olisa Agbakkogba vs FGN, NJC and national assembly, also the last according to him is Judiciary staff Union of Nigeria (JUSUN) vs NJC and Governor’s of 36 states”. ” Therefore, the organized labour is calling on the state government to look into the possibility of implementing the above decision”.